        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 5:31PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 531 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Stilesboro, or 7 miles
southwest of Cartersville, moving west at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Burnt Hickory Ridge, Cartersville, Euharlee, Stilesboro, and
Taylorsville.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
